wikipedia_page.main: Thomas Fair MacAulay McInnes (8 July 1873 – 1 December 1937) was a Scottish professional footballer.McInnes scored 65 goals from 246 appearances in the Football League playing as a forward for Nottingham Forest and Lincoln City. McInnes played in the Scottish Football League for Clyde and Port Glasgow Athletic,
